1
00:00:05,587 --> 00:00:08,754
(lightning crackling)

2
00:00:13,673 --> 00:00:15,533
(sighs) Yes, I know.

3
00:00:18,710 --> 00:00:20,046
Don't worry.

4
00:00:20,070 --> 00:00:24,483
I'll be there even if it means
sneaking out of the office.

5
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:26,806
Okay, okay.

6
00:00:26,830 --> 00:00:28,763
I'll talk to you later, huh?

7
00:00:30,350 --> 00:00:31,350
What?

8
00:00:32,150 --> 00:00:34,463
Can't say things like
that on an open line.

9
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:36,743
Someone might be listening.

10
00:00:38,780 --> 00:00:40,783
I'll see you at Memorial Low, all right?

11
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:45,350
For Christ's sake, she hung up on me.

12
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:48,130
Damn it.

13
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:51,525
Why does she always do that to me?

14
00:00:51,549 --> 00:00:53,873
Doesn't she know the stress I'm under?

15
00:00:53,897 --> 00:00:55,866
Crap, I forgot to ask her

16
00:00:55,890 --> 00:00:58,336
if it's a private hot spring or not.

17
00:00:58,360 --> 00:01:01,563
Ah well, it's time to
pick Yaegashi up anyway.

18
00:01:02,828 --> 00:01:05,661
(energetic music)

19
00:01:07,897 --> 00:01:12,230
(woman singing in foreign language)

20
00:01:23,420 --> 00:01:27,587
(man singing in foreign language)

21
00:01:37,057 --> 00:01:41,390
(woman singing in foreign language)

22
00:01:51,695 --> 00:01:55,945
(both singing in foreign language)

23
00:02:12,052 --> 00:02:15,969
♪ Just love ♪

24
00:02:16,928 --> 00:02:20,761
(singing in foreign language)

25
00:02:39,818 --> 00:02:42,651
(machine beeping)

26
00:02:43,928 --> 00:02:46,928
(suspenseful music)

27
00:02:53,987 --> 00:02:57,305
(water splashing)

28
00:02:57,329 --> 00:03:00,079
(birds chirping)

29
00:03:03,470 --> 00:03:05,887
(soft music)

30
00:03:08,670 --> 00:03:09,846
[Ryoko] This little oasis is the only

31
00:03:09,870 --> 00:03:12,366
open air hot spring for miles.

32
00:03:12,390 --> 00:03:14,886
Koume's grandfather built it himself.

33
00:03:14,910 --> 00:03:16,646
[Momiji] You don't say!

34
00:03:16,670 --> 00:03:17,480
[Koume] That's right.

35
00:03:17,504 --> 00:03:19,625
I used to play soldier in
this very spot all the time

36
00:03:19,649 --> 00:03:21,596
when I was a kid.

37
00:03:21,620 --> 00:03:22,906
[Ryoko] I didn't see it on any maps

38
00:03:22,930 --> 00:03:25,806
so we should have it all to ourselves.

39
00:03:25,830 --> 00:03:27,766
[Koume] Oh no one
knows about this place.

40
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:30,016
[Sakura] Yeah it really is
out in the boonies, isn't it?

41
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:32,976
[Koume] It may sound idyllic,
but try growing up here.

42
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:37,027
Oh look, monkeys!

43
00:03:37,051 --> 00:03:38,051
How cute!

44
00:03:38,890 --> 00:03:39,906
Look at them up here.

45
00:03:39,930 --> 00:03:42,186
Oh they're just ugly old monkeys.

46
00:03:42,210 --> 00:03:44,160
What's so exciting about that?

47
00:03:44,184 --> 00:03:47,134
(gasps) You've got to be kidding.

48
00:03:47,158 --> 00:03:48,476
They're adorable.

49
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:49,876
She can't help it.

50
00:03:49,900 --> 00:03:52,886
After all, all our friends
are monkeys you know.

51
00:03:52,910 --> 00:03:54,686
Ha ha, very funny,

52
00:03:54,710 --> 00:03:57,256
but I actually do know
how to speak monkey.

53
00:03:57,280 --> 00:04:00,442
Aw, why don't you let hear me a little.

54
00:04:00,466 --> 00:04:02,456
(whooping)

55
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:04,702
Oh, and how do you say one?

56
00:04:04,726 --> 00:04:05,535
Kee!

57
00:04:05,559 --> 00:04:06,368
And two?

58
00:04:06,392 --> 00:04:07,201
Ah-kee!

59
00:04:07,225 --> 00:04:08,074
Mhm?

60
00:04:08,098 --> 00:04:09,072
Ah-kee-kee.

61
00:04:09,096 --> 00:04:12,366
Valencia, go ahead and
take off your clothes

62
00:04:12,390 --> 00:04:13,596
and put 'em in the basket.

63
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:17,254
Ooh that doesn't look very secure to me.

64
00:04:17,278 --> 00:04:18,666
Are you sure?

65
00:04:18,690 --> 00:04:20,436
Yeah well amazingly,

66
00:04:20,460 --> 00:04:23,846
people used to trust total
strangers back in the old days.

67
00:04:23,870 --> 00:04:25,226
[Woman] How strange.

68
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:27,766
That must be one of
seven mysteries of Japan.

69
00:04:27,790 --> 00:04:29,646
[Woman] Gee, aren't we miss-know-it-all.

70
00:04:29,670 --> 00:04:31,410
Would you tell us the other six?

71
00:04:31,434 --> 00:04:36,069
Momiji, would you stop
playing around and hurry up?

72
00:04:36,093 --> 00:04:37,510
[Momiji] Ohkey!

73
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:43,163
- Hello up there!
- Hello.

74
00:04:44,540 --> 00:04:46,783
- May we join you?
- Of course.

75
00:04:48,150 --> 00:04:52,136
- This water looks wonderful.
- Is it too hot?

76
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,656
No, I didn't think so.

77
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,896
Do you think the water's too hot?

78
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:59,666
Oh no, hot water is
good for these old bones.

79
00:04:59,690 --> 00:05:02,063
Laziness will make a
woman weak, they say.

80
00:05:03,130 --> 00:05:05,886
[Ryoko] You know, Ishida
said the same thing!

81
00:05:05,910 --> 00:05:07,383
I must be getting soft.

82
00:05:11,548 --> 00:05:12,358
(dial tone beeping)

83
00:05:12,382 --> 00:05:14,036
You sure it's not too hot?

84
00:05:14,060 --> 00:05:15,216
It's just right.

85
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:18,826
Miss Takeuchi, it's your cellphone!

86
00:05:18,850 --> 00:05:20,346
Phone call!

87
00:05:20,370 --> 00:05:22,256
I'll get it.

88
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:23,736
Careful, it's hot.

89
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:25,556
We wouldn't want you to wilt.

90
00:05:25,580 --> 00:05:27,886
Yeah that's really funny.

91
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:30,334
How many times do I tell you, Valencia?

92
00:05:30,358 --> 00:05:33,393
Swimsuits are not meant for hot springs.

93
00:05:35,740 --> 00:05:37,046
Yeah, yeah, whatever.

94
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:39,943
You can just blame it
on my American modesty.

95
00:05:41,060 --> 00:05:42,696
Is that so?

96
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:44,336
Hi, who's calling?

97
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:45,736
[Yoshiki] Hello, it's Yaegashi!

98
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:47,266
Enjoying yourselves?

99
00:05:47,290 --> 00:05:48,896
Yes we are.

100
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:51,090
Have you wrapped things up yet?

101
00:05:51,114 --> 00:05:54,136
[Yoshiki] Yes, I think we'll
still be able to join you

102
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:57,237
by seven, if that's all right with you?

103
00:05:57,261 --> 00:06:00,189
(dial tone beeping)

104
00:06:00,213 --> 00:06:01,057
[Man] If she gabs any longer,

105
00:06:01,081 --> 00:06:02,673
I'll blow the thing right now.

106
00:06:05,650 --> 00:06:08,340
[Momoji] Those monkeys
sure are tame, aren't they?

107
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:11,905
No I think they're just
comfortable hanging around

108
00:06:11,929 --> 00:06:16,319
someone who knows how
to speak their language.

109
00:06:16,343 --> 00:06:18,956
What are you implying?

110
00:06:18,980 --> 00:06:21,346
- Sure act innocent.
- Oh-key.

111
00:06:21,370 --> 00:06:23,936
What you say you learned how to juggle?

112
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:26,216
[Yoshiki] Yes, and I'm looking forward

113
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:28,896
to showing off my talents
at the party tonight.

114
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,113
What a riot.

115
00:06:30,137 --> 00:06:32,515
I can't wait.

116
00:06:32,539 --> 00:06:35,156
(cellphone ringing)

117
00:06:35,180 --> 00:06:36,696
Hello?

118
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:39,678
[Man] You're lucky you
didn't blab any longer.

119
00:06:39,702 --> 00:06:42,406
Huh, who am I talking to?

120
00:06:42,430 --> 00:06:43,846
[Man] I've placed a
bomb in the hot spring

121
00:06:43,870 --> 00:06:45,773
your friends are bathing in right now.

122
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:50,456
[Ryoko] Is this a joke?

123
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:52,306
[Man] The bomb will
be activated the instant

124
00:06:52,330 --> 00:06:54,616
the water hits a certain level.

125
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:56,877
Ah, if that level were to change, boom.

126
00:06:57,980 --> 00:07:01,204
I don't believe one
word of this hogwash.

127
00:07:01,228 --> 00:07:03,380
[Man] Fine, don't believe me.

128
00:07:03,404 --> 00:07:04,566
Just thought you should know

129
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:06,216
the triggering device will be set

130
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:09,250
the instant that sweet
thing slips into the pool.

131
00:07:12,470 --> 00:07:13,279
Stop!

132
00:07:13,303 --> 00:07:14,303
Valencia.

133
00:07:15,961 --> 00:07:18,795
(dramatic music)

134
00:07:18,819 --> 00:07:20,951
No one, no one move a muscle.

135
00:07:20,975 --> 00:07:23,426
[Koume] Did someone lose
their contacts or something?

136
00:07:23,450 --> 00:07:26,316
Okay, listen up everyone.

137
00:07:26,340 --> 00:07:29,256
Whatever you do, do not stand up.

138
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:30,560
Do you hear me?

139
00:07:30,584 --> 00:07:32,011
I just received a call

140
00:07:32,035 --> 00:07:34,816
claiming there's a bomb in the springs.

141
00:07:34,840 --> 00:07:35,747
A bomb?

142
00:07:35,771 --> 00:07:37,426
All the way out here?

143
00:07:37,450 --> 00:07:40,143
Apparently it's activated
by the water level.

144
00:07:41,970 --> 00:07:43,780
I don't know whether it's true or not,

145
00:07:43,804 --> 00:07:47,736
but until we're absolutely sure, we'll...

146
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:50,366
Excuse me, does that include us?

147
00:07:50,390 --> 00:07:54,216
Yes, I'm afraid you're going
to have to stay in the water.

148
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,593
In the water?

149
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:59,697
What about Momiji's bathing buddies?

150
00:08:01,797 --> 00:08:04,714
(suspicious music)

151
00:08:05,647 --> 00:08:07,646
Koume, can you catch them?

152
00:08:07,670 --> 00:08:09,326
Why do I have to do everything?

153
00:08:09,350 --> 00:08:11,404
Momiji, let's go.

154
00:08:11,428 --> 00:08:12,428
Why me?

155
00:08:13,463 --> 00:08:14,746
[Koume] They're your friends.

156
00:08:14,770 --> 00:08:15,833
That's just great.

157
00:08:16,910 --> 00:08:19,123
Say hi to your pals for me.

158
00:08:19,147 --> 00:08:22,064
See you (mumbles).

159
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:25,763
(foreboding music)

160
00:08:25,787 --> 00:08:28,996
Okay Momiji, reach under
water and grab their feet

161
00:08:29,020 --> 00:08:30,896
so they can't see you coming.

162
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:34,313
It's impossible to catch
a wild monkey barehanded.

163
00:08:36,137 --> 00:08:39,812
(foreboding music)

164
00:08:39,836 --> 00:08:40,836
Key.

165
00:08:42,260 --> 00:08:43,326
[Koume] You ready?

166
00:08:43,350 --> 00:08:46,276
We're gonna grab them
on the count of three.

167
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:47,939
You got it?

168
00:08:47,963 --> 00:08:49,183
Key.

169
00:08:49,207 --> 00:08:51,410
One, two, and three.

170
00:08:53,406 --> 00:08:56,967
Stay still, don't panic you stupid monkey.

171
00:08:56,991 --> 00:08:58,438
Will you stay still?

172
00:08:58,462 --> 00:08:59,272
Oh my.

173
00:08:59,296 --> 00:09:01,628
Oh are you having trouble?

174
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:05,159
[Koume] How come yours is so tame, ow!

175
00:09:05,183 --> 00:09:08,546
I don't know, just friends I guess.

176
00:09:08,570 --> 00:09:12,226
Are you sure we can really
trust those two jokers?

177
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:14,363
Oh they're more serious than they look.

178
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:15,453
Don't worry about it.

179
00:09:18,490 --> 00:09:21,956
So tell us, have you
learned anything so far?

180
00:09:21,980 --> 00:09:24,396
Yes, I sure did.

181
00:09:24,420 --> 00:09:26,656
The float is being used as a switch,

182
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:29,123
attached to a pack of explosives nearby.

183
00:09:29,147 --> 00:09:31,989
He must be pretty confident
we can't disarm it

184
00:09:32,013 --> 00:09:35,046
because it sure was easy to find.

185
00:09:35,070 --> 00:09:37,636
So what do you think we can do about it?

186
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:40,680
Well I suppose, what??

187
00:09:42,275 --> 00:09:43,811
Huh, what was that?

188
00:09:43,835 --> 00:09:48,404
(explosion booming)
(foreboding music)

189
00:09:48,428 --> 00:09:50,095
Close to the road.

190
00:09:51,580 --> 00:09:53,188
What is it?

191
00:09:53,212 --> 00:09:56,876
[Man] So do you still
think this is hogwash?

192
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:58,543
[Ryoko] What do you want?

193
00:10:00,210 --> 00:10:01,609
[Man] Not a lot.

194
00:10:01,633 --> 00:10:04,886
Just 50 million.

195
00:10:04,910 --> 00:10:07,186
We aren't worth much, are we?

196
00:10:07,210 --> 00:10:08,363
You hurt my feelings.

197
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,396
Oh I'm sorry.

198
00:10:10,420 --> 00:10:12,836
I meant in US dollars.

199
00:10:12,860 --> 00:10:14,066
Dollars?

200
00:10:14,090 --> 00:10:14,937
What?

201
00:10:14,961 --> 00:10:16,896
Can't you do multiplication?

202
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:20,096
What do you mean, that's
more than five billion yen.

203
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,906
We are so dead.

204
00:10:21,930 --> 00:10:24,536
Oh yeah, that's about
what I'd go for these days.

205
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:25,886
You think so?

206
00:10:25,910 --> 00:10:27,759
What are we, spare change?

207
00:10:27,783 --> 00:10:30,896
She really doesn't know any.

208
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:32,766
The bag of unmarked hundred dollar bills

209
00:10:32,790 --> 00:10:35,006
should be ready in three hours.

210
00:10:35,030 --> 00:10:37,546
You'll hear from me in 10 minutes.

211
00:10:37,570 --> 00:10:38,883
Hold on a minute.

212
00:10:43,507 --> 00:10:46,323
- (telephone ringing)
- Hello.

213
00:10:47,247 --> 00:10:48,876
This is Kunikida.

214
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:50,793
Ah, how's the vacation going?

215
00:10:51,770 --> 00:10:53,396
What kind of bomb?

216
00:10:53,420 --> 00:10:56,066
Wha, a bomb?

217
00:10:56,090 --> 00:10:57,163
Are you sure?

218
00:10:58,314 --> 00:11:01,603
I wonder what's going
to become of us now.

219
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:04,896
Oh Momiji, shit happens, life goes on.

220
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:05,933
What can you do?

221
00:11:06,783 --> 00:11:07,783
Oh.

222
00:11:08,883 --> 00:11:11,875
I wish Kusanagi were here.

223
00:11:11,899 --> 00:11:15,440
(birds chirping)

224
00:11:15,464 --> 00:11:17,921
(Momiji gasps)

225
00:11:17,945 --> 00:11:19,129
Did someone call me?

226
00:11:19,153 --> 00:11:21,049
(triumphant music)

227
00:11:21,073 --> 00:11:22,073
Kusa.

228
00:11:23,780 --> 00:11:25,796
Another one of your
monkey friends, Momiji?

229
00:11:25,820 --> 00:11:29,133
You know I never let you
out of my sight, Momiji.

230
00:11:30,510 --> 00:11:31,327
Greetings.

231
00:11:31,351 --> 00:11:32,846
Now I'll need your help.

232
00:11:32,870 --> 00:11:34,624
Sure, so where do you need me?

233
00:11:34,648 --> 00:11:36,471
I'll need you in the hot spring.

234
00:11:36,495 --> 00:11:37,516
Huh?

235
00:11:37,540 --> 00:11:38,656
[Ryoko] To defuse that bomb,

236
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:40,526
I'll need someone who knows explosives

237
